- \(P(\text{neither}) = 0.08\)
- \(P(P) = P(C) + 0.16\)

The probability of visiting at least one is \(1 - P(\text{neither}) = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92\). Using the formula for the union:
\[
P(P \text{ or } C) = P(P) + P(C) - P(\text{both})
\]
Substitute the known values:
\[
