- 19% have low blood pressure.
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat.
- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure.
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat.

First, the percentage with normal blood pressure is calculated as 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.

Next, the number of patients with irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is found: 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95%.

Then, the number with irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure: 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.

The total with irregular heartbeat is 17%, so the number with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure is: 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.

The percentage with low blood pressure is 19%, which includes both regular and irregular heartbeats. Therefore, the percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat is: 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.

Rounding 15.10% to one decimal place (based on the input percentages having mostly two significant figures) gives 15.1%.

