Solution: The probability of at least one match when rolling a fair $n$-sided die $n$ independent times is given by $1 - \left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right)^n$. As $n$ approaches infinity, this probability converges to $1 - \frac{1}{e}$, where $e \approx 2.718281828459$.

