\[
S \approx (1.0545718 \times 10^{-34}) \times 0.8660254 = 9.13286 \times 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s}.
\]

Rounded to three significant figures, the result is \( 9.13 \times 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s} \). Therefore, the numerical coefficient for the unit \( 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s} \) is 9.13.

